      "[Crawling Shore, Ebon Sands]"
    ],
    "description": [
      "Gleaming mica and bits of quartz wink from the black sands that consume the path toward the shoreline.  The powdery grit rolls in low, wave-like dunes and is strewn here and there with bits of bone and whole shells.  To the northwest, on a low bluff above the bleakness of the beach, a quiet village shelters beneath an uncaring sky."
